olive oil
1 corn
2 Burger Bun
1 avocado
1 packet beef mince
1 sachet Kiwi Spice Blend
1 packet fine breadcrumbs
1 egg
1 packet Mixed Salad Leaves
drizzle white wine vinegar
20 g butter
1 packet mayonnaise

• Preheat BBQ to high heat.
• Halve corn and burger buns.
• Slice avocado in half, scoop out flesh and thinly
slice. Season with salt and pepper.

• In a large bowl, combine beef mince, Kiwi spice
blend, fine breadcrumbs and the egg.
• Shape beef mixture into 2cm-thick patties
(1 per person).

• When BBQ is hot, add corn and cook,
turning, until charred and cooked through,
10-15 minutes.
• Transfer to a plate and cover to keep warm.

NO BBQ? Half-fill a medium saucepan with water
and bring to the boil. Cook corn in boiling water
until tender and bright yellow, 5 minutes. Cover to
keep warm.

• Meanwhile, grill beef patties for 3-5 minutes
each side, until charred and cooked through.

NO BBQ? Cook beef patties in a frying pan over high
heat, 4-5 minutes each side.

• When the patties are done, grill buns, cut-side
down, until lightly golden, 2-3 minutes.

NO BBQ? Grill or toast buns to your liking.

• In a medium bowl, combine mixed salad leaves
and a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil.
• Top corn with the butter.
• Spread burger buns with mayonnaise, then top
with a flamegrilled smokey beef patty, avocado
and salad leaves.
• Serve with buttered corn cob. Enjoy!